                            Forschungsumgebung / Beta maṣāḥǝft,  Akademie der Wissenschaften in Hamburg</dc:publisher><dcterms:isPartOf rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu"/><dcterms:bibliographicCitation>LIT7525MAAZaraY</dcterms:bibliographicCitation><dc:format>xml</dc:format><dc:language rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#language">en</dc:language><dc:language rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#language">gez</dc:language><dc:contributor>Alessandro Bausi</dc:contributor><dc:contributor>Dorothea Reule</dc:contributor><rdf:type rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/ChristianLiterature"/><rdf:type rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/Hagiography"/><rdf:type rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/Miracle"/><dc:title>Miracle of ʾAbrǝhā and ʾAṣbǝḥa: King Zarʿa Yāʿqob decides an argument between the priests of Gamād and the priests of ʾAksum on the tithe in favour of the priests of ʾAksum, but after the intervention of ʾAbrǝhā and ʾAṣbǝḥa he changes his decisions and lets the priests of Gamād benefit from their ancient privileges</dc:title><dc:title xml:lang="en">Miracle of ʾAbrǝhā and ʾAṣbǝḥa: King Zarʿa Yāʿqob decides an argument between the priests of Gamād and the priests of ʾAksum on the tithe in favour of the priests of ʾAksum, but after the intervention of ʾAbrǝhā and ʾAṣbǝḥa he changes his decisions and lets the priests of Gamād benefit from their ancient privileges</dc:title><crm:P102_has_title rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7525MAAZaraY/title/t1" xml:lang="en"/><dcterms:hasPart rdf:resource="LIT7525MAAZaraY/part/div1"/></rdf:Description><rdf:Description rdf:about="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7525MAAZaraY"><ecrm:P129_is_about rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1284Abrehaa"/></rdf:Description><rdf:Description rdf:about="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7525MAAZaraY"><ecrm:P129_is_about rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS2100Asbeha"/></rdf:Description><rdf:Description rdf:about="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7525MAAZaraY"><ecrm:P129_is_about rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1263Abraha"/></rdf:Description><rdf:Description rdf:about="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7525MAAZaraY"><ecrm:P129_is_about rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10626ZaraY"/></rdf:Description><rdf:Description rdf:about="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7525MAAZaraY"><ecrm:CLP46i_may_form_part_of rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7510HagDosAA"/></rdf:Description><rdf:Description rdf:about="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7525MAAZaraY"><ecrm:CLP46i_may_form_part_of rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7511TaammeraAA"/></rdf:Description><rdf:Description rdf:about="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7525MAAZaraY/part/div1"><dcterms:isPartOf rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7525MAAZaraY"/><rdf:type rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/part"/><dc:relation rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/https://betamasaheft.eu/ANLcr19"/></rdf:Description><rdf:Description rdf:about="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7525MAAZaraY/title/t1"><rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/E35_Title"/><rdfs:label>Miracle of ʾAbrǝhā and ʾAṣbǝḥa: King Zarʿa Yāʿqob decides an argument between the priests of Gamād and the priests of ʾAksum on the tithe in favour of the priests of ʾAksum, but after the intervention of ʾAbrǝhā and ʾAṣbǝḥa he changes his decisions and lets the priests of Gamād benefit from their ancient privileges</rdfs:label></rdf:Description></rdf:RDF>